
1. go to https://console.cloud.google.com and get a free server.
2. Read
  https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/instances/connecting-advanced#thirdpartytools
  https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/instances/adding-removing-ssh-keys#edit-ssh-metadata

3. Create your private key on your local box.
4. Copy it to the metadata section for ssh keys for your instance. You
   will have to edit the setting for the instance. This will create the user
   in the ssh pub key.
5. Login to the new user created. Follow normal ssh authorized_users
   instructions for ssh. Basically copy the pub key into ~.ssh/auithorized_users
   and make it chmod 600 on that file.
6. ssh -i .ssh/PRIVATE_KEY USER@<IP ADDRESS>
   NOTE: Your ip address may change with reboots. You will have to login to
   the google webpage for the instance to find out the ip address.
   
   
